SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 139
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to recognize Nancy Harmon on the occasion of
her retirement.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that the members of this General Assembly should honor
those citizens who have performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm throughout their
years of industry; and
WHEREAS, Nancy Harmon is one such estimable individual, who, having rendered
twenty-two years of distinguished service to Heritage Center, has taken her much-deserved
retirement; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Harmon served Heritage Center with acumen and alacrity as the
human resources manager, in which position she earned the respect and admiration of her
colleagues and community alike for the superior quality of her work; and
WHEREAS, with nearly four decades of experience in human resources, Mrs. Harmon
began her estimable career at the former Anchor Brush Plant in 1986; she went on to work for
the Performance Food Group Company and the Life Care Center of Morristown before joining
Heritage Center in 2002; and
WHEREAS, her professional accomplishments aside, Nancy Harmon is most grateful for
the love and support of her husband, Mark, whom she met at Heritage Center, and her sons,
Tyler and Tyson; and
WHEREAS, throughout her estimable career, Mrs. Harmon remained committed to the
mission of the Heritage Center, and she has demonstrated the utmost professionalism, ability,
and integrity; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
